# UI Components Guide

AiWeb comes with a comprehensive set of reusable UI components built with DaisyUI. This guide covers all available components and how to use them.

## Button Component

The Button component provides a flexible way to create interactive buttons with various styles.

### Basic Usage

```astro
---
import Button from '@/components/ui/Button.astro';
---

<Button variant="primary">Click me</Button>
<Button variant="secondary" outline>Outlined</Button>
<Button variant="accent" size="lg">Large Button</Button>
```

### Props

- `variant`: primary, secondary, accent, ghost, link, info, success, warning, error
- `size`: xs, sm, md, lg
- `outline`: boolean
- `wide`: boolean
- `block`: boolean
- `glass`: boolean
- `href`: string (makes it a link)

## Card Component

Cards are perfect for displaying content in a contained format.

### Basic Usage

```astro
---
import Card from '@/components/ui/Card.astro';
---

<Card
  title="Card Title"
  description="Card description goes here"
  image="/images/card.jpg"
  href="/link"
/>
```

### Props

- `title`: string
- `description`: string
- `image`: string
- `imageAlt`: string
- `href`: string
- `bordered`: boolean
- `compact`: boolean
- `side`: boolean (side-by-side layout)
- `glass`: boolean
- `hover`: boolean (hover effect)

## Hero Component

Create stunning hero sections with ease.

### Basic Usage

```astro
---
import Hero from '@/components/ui/Hero.astro';
import Button from '@/components/ui/Button.astro';
---

<Hero
  title="Welcome to AiWeb"
  subtitle="Build amazing websites"
>
  <Button variant="primary" size="lg">Get Started</Button>
</Hero>
```

### Props

- `title`: string (required)
- `subtitle`: string
- `image`: string (background image)
- `overlay`: boolean
- `gradient`: boolean
- `centered`: boolean

