## DaisyUI Components

In addition to our custom components, you have access to all DaisyUI components:

### Alerts

```html
<div class="alert alert-success">
  <svg>...</svg>
  <span>Your purchase has been confirmed!</span>
</div>
```

### Badges

```html
<span class="badge badge-primary">Primary</span>
<span class="badge badge-secondary">Secondary</span>
<span class="badge badge-accent">Accent</span>
```

### Modal

```html
<button class="btn" onclick="my_modal.showModal()">Open Modal</button>
<dialog id="my_modal" class="modal">
  <div class="modal-box">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg">Hello!</h3>
    <p class="py-4">Modal content here</p>
  </div>
</dialog>
```

### Loading Spinners

```html
<span class="loading loading-spinner loading-lg"></span>
<span class="loading loading-dots loading-lg"></span>
<span class="loading loading-ring loading-lg"></span>
```

## Styling Tips

### Custom Classes

All components accept a `class` prop for custom styling:

```astro
<Button class="my-4 mx-auto" variant="primary">
  Custom Styled Button
</Button>
```

### Responsive Design

Use Tailwind's responsive modifiers:

```html
<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
  <!-- Cards go here -->
</div>
```

### Animations

Apply animations with utility classes:

```html
<div class="card card-hover animate-pulse">
  <!-- Animated card -->
</div>
```

## Best Practices

1. **Reuse components**: Don't recreate what already exists
2. **Consistent spacing**: Use the spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, etc.)
3. **Accessibility**: Always include proper ARIA labels
4. **Mobile first**: Design for mobile, then enhance for larger screens
5. **Theme aware**: Test your components in different themes

